title: Ahsaas
subTitle: After being rejected by their fathers, Raju and Anu elope and get settled in a village but when the parents learn about their whereabouts, they decide to bring them back.

title: Sita Ram Chaddha
subTitle: Sita Ram Chaddha's married daughter has the option to seek financial help from her brother. However, she has a unique request that transforms the lives of everyone.

title: #Goals
subTitle: After some time apart, Meera and Ranbir find their relationship at a point where it becomes a perfect example of the shallowness and fragility of modern-day dating.

title: A Tale Of An Onion Witch Chapter 2
subTitle: A newlywed couple encounters a woman claiming to be Mangla, who cautions them about an ancient witch roaming the area at night in search of onions. However, the situation takes an unexpected turn when a young girl desperately seeks assistance by knocking on their door at the stroke of midnight, plunging the couple into a potentially perilous scenario.

title: Half Cake
subTitle: A poor single mother struggles fiercely to earn the extra money needed to fulfill her child's simple wish for a cake just like the one he saw in a shop.

title: Harshit
subTitle: Fate plays a twisted game with Harshit and Rahila, who are madly in love with each other.

title: Love Ishtory
subTitle: A man from an upper caste learns that his daughter is in love with a man from a lower caste. While he beats up the man, a police officer encourages him to continue his assault.

title: Pilibhit
subTitle: Siraj, a poor flute maker, resides in the forest of Pilibhit, known for its man-eating tigers. Soon, his poverty and the tragedies in his life threaten to break his values.

title: 10.30 Lets Go To School
subTitle: A determined village girl struggles to attend school as her family expects her to stay home, but her love for learning drives her to find clever ways to keep studying.

title: Dum Dum Deega Deega
subTitle: Ajju, the son of a drunkard beggar, lives on the streets of Mumbai but holds a positive outlook towards life. He refuses to beg and tries to earn money through respectable means.

title: Aakhri Kahani
subTitle: A desperate writer plans one final movie pitch to a producer. However, he ends up driving the producer in his taxi, giving him an unexpected opportunity to share his idea during the ride.

title: Abba Ki Chaddi
subTitle: A troubled housewife, weary and worn down by her husband's numerous past misdeeds, finally seeks the retribution she believes is long overdue.

title: In Your Arms
subTitle: After 14 years, Nikhil tells Payal he wants a divorce, confessing love for a colleague. Payal agrees, but only on one condition.

title: Love Bites
subTitle: Karthik and Meghna flaunt their hickeys, making their sexual chemistry obvious to everyone.

title: Panch Din
subTitle: A married couple, meeting in a caf√© to finalise their divorce, is unexpectedly joined by a mutual friend. However, they begin to rethink their decision after the friend reminds them of a past event.

title: Thanks Mom
subTitle: Two brothers, who are aspiring filmmakers, are forced to use their mother's fund to make their film. However, disagreements arise when their mother does not approve the contents of the film.

title: Abnormal
subTitle: A mother fights for her transgender son's future and freedom, striving for acceptance and harmony from her family and society.

title: Dubki
subTitle: Dubki is a story based on a true incident of a female constable in male-dominated law enforcement. Despite being a tough and dominant constable at the Lalkurti police station, Ganga Yadav was troubled several times by SHO Durgesh Mishra. Ganga complained about it to the IPS officer and asked for a transfer; however, he refused to help her. The female constable was left with no other choice but to take justice into her own hands.

title: Dwand
subTitle: Ruby, raised to believe in her potential, however, finds herself married to a traditional man, Vivek. After motherhood, she decides to pursue an advertising career, sparking unforeseen troubles.

title: Once Upon A Time In Office
subTitle: Once Upon A Time In Office

title: Baggage
subTitle: Sara's twin sister disappears in a bizarre manner, leaving her to deal with the loss. However, when she is unable to come to terms with it, Sara decides to find answers.

title: Bully
subTitle: A girl holds her brother hostage, however, she must confront the dark side of her life and face the harsh truths that threaten to break her.

title: Beyond Failing
subTitle: A young student struggles with academic pressure due to poor performance. However, she sets out on a path of self-discovery and soon finds her true passion.

title: Bhagwaan - The Faith
subTitle: A routine gym outing for three friends becomes a series of unusual interactions with diverse strangers. Their day reaches a pivotal moment when they cross paths with an enigmatic street dweller.

title: Bhagwaan - The Faith
subTitle: A routine gym outing for three friends becomes a series of unusual interactions with diverse strangers. Their day reaches a pivotal moment when they cross paths with an enigmatic street dweller.

title: Bridge
subTitle: Widower Mukesh lives with son Rahul, 28. Rahul finds his father's behavior odd and Mukesh resents his son's constant judgment of his choices.

title: Calling Bell
subTitle: A demented delivery man forces himself inside the house of a young lady, threatening to kill her. However, the confrontation takes an unusual turn when the true nature of his visit is revealed.

title: Saanjh
subTitle: SAANJH tells the story of Shyam and Sandhya, childhood friends who meet for the last time. Shyam loves Sandhya, but she sees him only as a friend. We surprisingly learn that Shyam is actually struggling with mental disorder, and Sandhya is nothing but just in his imagination. Despite the calm riverbank setting, Shyam's inner struggles are evident. As Shyam faces reality, he realizes he must accept things as they are, showing the power of love and understanding ourselves.

title: Samaapan
subTitle: An impoverished vocalist named Avik faces financial hardships as he tries to provide for his family while attempting to win over his love, Shukla.

title: Life 2.0
subTitle: A nature lover pushes her ambitious human resettlement proposal to a world that is not ready for it. However, a data-related catastrophe may change everything.

title: Khalish
subTitle: A girl whose childhood is marred by violent household disputes grows up feeling helpless and anxious, developing hostility towards authority and triggering colossal consequences.

title: Duty
subTitle: Individuals from different walks of life and social classes demonstrate the interdependence of each social stratum on the other through their duties and responsibilities.

title: The Decision
subTitle: The Struggle of an Actress in the Film Industry: A young woman faces difficulties when working with a demanding director who creates a stressful environment. She expresses her concerns to the producer, but he reacts angrily and uses harsh language toward her. Will the actress decide to find a way to work together or stand up for herself?

title: Choices
subTitle: Just one day before their wedding, Ritesh confesses something to Yami that threatens to change the course of their relationship.

title: Days Left Behind
subTitle: In a world infested by cannibalistic zombies, a man finds himself stranded inside his house. However, when he hears a car crash, he discovers that he is not alone.

title: Destiny's Two
subTitle: A man newly married to a dwarf decides to go to a red-light area to fulfill his desire for a taller woman.

title: Charitra Varnan
subTitle: A cab driver's kind attempt to help a weeping woman who dashed out of her house after a fight with her husband goes terribly wrong.

title: First Sin
subTitle: What would you do if you unexpectedly obtain magical powers? Ashwath, a failed businessman is having a troubled relationship with his wife. One fine morning he gets a Sand-timer at his doorstep. Life takes a turn when he discovers magical powers in it. Will the Sand-timer be a boon or curse?

title: Girl in Red
subTitle: A writer who is struggling with writer's block is in search of a story. However, he lands himself in trouble when he stumbles upon a deadly secret while talking to his garbage collector.

title: Harmless
subTitle: A boy in need of money to make it big in life and a girl who is looking for thrill concoct a plan and stage a kidnapping to extort money from the girl's rich father.

title: Laxmi
subTitle: A maid is shocked to find the owner of the house where she works dead. Upon telling her partner, he plans a scheme to rob the house.

title: Tithlee
subTitle: A newly wedded woman faces colourism from her mother-in-law. While her husband wants to fight this prejudice, she decides to navigate it and maintain her dignity within the family.

title: U=Me
subTitle: Nikita and Neeraj share a long-standing acquaintance, yet she feels uncomfortable with Neeraj's physical contact. Adding to her dilemma, Aniket has recently proposed to her.

title: Jaane Do Mujhe
subTitle: During a seemingly pleasant date with Aditya, arranged by her friends, Nisha hears a concerning noise from the washroom. She discovers Aditya unconscious on the floor and immediately calls her friend Priya for help. Surprisingly, Priya dismisses Nisha's concerns, suggesting it's all imaginary. This unexpected response casts doubt on Aditya's existence and the reality of the entire situation, leaving Nisha confused about what's real and what might be a product of her imagination.

title: The Last Act
subTitle: Chitra, a method actor known for her ability to deliver realistic performances, starts preparing for her next role. However, things take a dark turn when the intensity of her character and her desire to excel in her work cause her to lose touch with reality.

title: The Friend To Die For
subTitle: The abduction of a young girl by a serial killer takes an unforeseen turn as revelations emerge, challenging initial assumptions about the case.

title: Exchange Offer
subTitle: Shiv lives alone, writing poetry on an old computer that breaks down. However, a service visit arranged by his son brings unexpected nostalgia, surprises and an intriguing exchange offer.

title: Faboo
subTitle: Are we using social media to expand our horizon or are we overusing it and unknowingly desensitizing ourselves? Faboo explores this aspect of social media and nudges us to think about it through this story of a mother and son.

title: Firki
subTitle: As a family decides to go for a drive, the father stays adamant on driving. His views on technology lead him to not trust navigational systems, but he himself struggles with directions.

title: Happily Married Part 2
subTitle: Rani and Animesh, a couple who is having an affair with Jimmy plan to meet him on Saturday. The story unfolds as their meeting with Jimmy doesn't go as planned.

title: Ruk Jana Nahi
subTitle: A withdrawn young man living with his father begins to regain purpose when a wedding next door brings people noise and quiet moments of unexpected hope.

title: Antahkaran
subTitle: A devout Hindu's quest for vengeance is complicated by his two friends with conflicting ideologies, both of whom attempt to manipulate his actions.

title: Anu Aur Di
subTitle: After a heated breakup, an angry girl calls her older sister for a late-night pickup. However, they soon get into a fight and are pulled over by the police.

title: Bahar Aa Chaman Prakash
subTitle: Bahar Aa Chaman Prakash delves into the story of a man reluctant to marry his lifelong acquaintance. Shutting himself away and avoiding his father, he faces the girl his father wishes him to wed. When she joins him and locks themselves in a room, they emerge with a revelation connected to the man's inner struggles. Will his father embrace this truth?

title: Dry Dreams
subTitle: A man dreams about having a beautiful woman by his side. However, his desire soon causes his life to take an unexpected turn.

title: Two Strangers
subTitle: A man with a scientific background deals with a mysterious health condition. However, destiny intervenes and cures his issue.

title: Chashmadeed
subTitle: An ageing mother, living with her entitled son and his wife, finds her sight blurring and clearing like a malfunctioning camera lens one morning. Soon, a visit to a nearby eye clinic, strongly suggested by her young neighbour, leads to unexpected revelations.

title: Dadi Ka Murabba
subTitle: A young, simple village man looking to start a business and earn a name for himself is encouraged and supported by his grandmother to achieve his dream.

title: Date Night
subTitle: A woman lovingly plans an elaborate date night for her husband. However, things go downhill when he is unable to make it.

title: Hearts Awash In Sapphire Light
subTitle: Hearts Awash in Sapphire Light unfolds the tale of two individuals who encounter each other one evening, initially under less-than-ideal circumstances. At first, they engage in petty arguments over trivial matters. However, as time passes, the undeniable power of their connection becomes evident, serving as a poignant reminder that sometimes, the most extraordinary journeys take place within the depths of our own hearts.

title: Humraz
subTitle: This is the story of a couple who tried to raise their voice against the undesirable practice of one community. Hamraz is a witness to the hero playing Ravanahatha and the incidents that happened to him... Sometimes the image that looks white is also black... Hamraz is a story full of mysteries... The curtain will soon fall on all the secrets and the real story will come out in front of everyone.

title: Jama Punji
subTitle: A late night conversation between a mother (Sarla) & her son Anshuman, 13 days after the passing of his father where they discuss the reasons for his detachment from his father and how by the end of the night, certain events lead Anshuman to accept and make amends with his deceased father.

title: Kidnapped
subTitle: Shruti, a spoiled rich girl, dislikes her father's strict behaviour towards her. Later, she and her boyfriend, Aakash, devise a plan to kidnap her to help her escape his strict parenting.

title: Loha Chor
subTitle: A modest family from Haryana relocated to Dhanbad, Bihar, and took up residence in a government quarter that had previously been inhabited by the notorious Loha Chor gang during the 1980s in Bihar. The family encountered numerous challenges and social difficulties from both the local neighbourhood inhabitants and the remnants of the Loha Chor gang. Subsequently, law enforcement authorities conducted a raid on the premises.

title: Meri Ramma Sabse Special
subTitle: Vikrant returns home after 15 years, confronting unresolved tensions with his mother. He faces painful truths and rekindles old wounds, searching for answers to heal their fractured relationship. However, Vikrant must reconcile with his past to build a brighter future.

title: Naam Badal Dena
subTitle: Lifelong friends turned spouses navigate moments of doubt reassurance and reflection that reveal the depth of their connection and what true partnership requires.

title: Ode To The Nameless
subTitle: A 24-year-old man, feeling the weight of societal expectations, decides to take an unconventional step in his search for intimacy. His choice leads him down an unexpected path, filled with awkward moments and conflicting emotions. What begins as a straightforward transaction evolves into a profound learning experience, guided by an unexpectedly wise companion.

title: Black Coffee
subTitle: A woman faces sexual harassment at the hands of her boss. Later, she decides to teach him a lesson with the help of her colleague.

title: Fear Of Wheels
subTitle: Follow the emotional struggle between ambitious youth and weary elders facing the grip of old age as they endure the pain of losing independence and becoming reliant on others.

title: Meera
subTitle: A mother calls out to her daughter, only to be scolded by her husband. Her daughter, Meera, is a special child who cannot speak or hear, yet her mother sends her to school with hope. Despite the chaos and negativity around her, Meera remains unaware, finding beauty and positivity in everything.

title: O Re Saajan
subTitle: A mid-thirties property broker in Lucknow named Sajan Tiwari engages in an illicit liaison, only to be discovered by his five-year-old son Bunty. Subsequently, Sajan becomes frantic in his attempts to prevent Bunty from divulging this information to his spouse Manju, resulting in a lighthearted depiction of provincial life, interpersonal bonds, and domestic affairs.

title: Unfinished Business
subTitle: A mother loves her child dearly, which gives the latter the strength and courage to overcome various obstacles and face fears.

title: Aam Ka Achaar
subTitle: Haunted by the riots that took his parents 20 years ago, Karan confronts the man who once loved him as a son-yet betrayed him in the worst way. Torn between revenge and forgiveness, he seeks meaning in the madness. A powerful story of loss, betrayal, and the fight for redemption.

title: Adarniya Mantri Ji
subTitle: Finance Minister and her secretary seize black money, yet half goes missing. Later, the secretary reveals he's behind the theft as part of a secret plan. The story ends unresolved.

title: The Red Suitcase
subTitle: A cab driver's quiet routine is shattered when she picks up an apparently innocuous passenger carrying a red suitcase. What starts off as a simple ride soon turns into a twisted journey.
